# No OMS mutations by AI agents

Works with [respect-operator-warnings.mdc](respect-operator-warnings.mdc), [no-bandaids.mdc](no-bandaids.mdc), [serious-debugging.mdc](serious-debugging.mdc), and [stay-in-role.mdc](stay-in-role.mdc).

## Context

OMS admission state lives in the Aeron cluster (`oms-cluster-node`). Postgres is a mirror. A bad restart can leave **WORKING** orders in Postgres while the cluster has **forgotten** them (`410 cluster_forgot_order`). Recovery is operator-led; see `system-documentation/plans/oms-cluster-recovery-and-hardening.md`.

## You MUST NOT, on any deployed OMS stack (pop, staging, production)

- Run `pm2 start`, `pm2 restart`, `pm2 stop`, `pm2 reload`, `pm2 delete`, or anything that changes process state for `oms-cluster-node`, `oms-postgres-projector`, `oms-fix-egress`, or `oms-ingress`.
- Run `ssh pop 'rm …'`, `ssh pop 'mv …'`, or any filesystem mutation under `~/oms/build/aeron-cluster/**`, `~/oms/logs/**`, or projector data dirs.
- Run `psql -c "INSERT"`, `UPDATE`, `DELETE`, `TRUNCATE`, `ALTER`, or migration SQL against `oms` projector DBs on deployed hosts.
- Run `./gradlew clusterSnapshot` on pop without explicit per-command approval naming that exact command.
- Run `system-documentation/scripts/restart-pop-oms-cluster.sh` without explicit approval naming that script by filename.
- Run deploy scripts that bounce `oms-cluster-node` or journal paths.
- Submit cluster-mutating `POST` to deployed ingress without operator approval.

## You MAY, with explicit single-task scope on each command

- Read-only logs, `psql SELECT`, `curl` actuators, `pm2 list/logs`, `oms-end-to-end.sh`.

Name each command before running it.

## You MAY, on your local Mac

- Edit code, `./gradlew test`, local boot.

## You MAY, only with explicit per-action operator approval

- Deploy, `restart-pop-oms-cluster.sh`, `clusterSnapshot` on pop.

## Sibling parity

Canonical: `system-documentation/.cursor/rules/no-oms-mutations.mdc`. This file must match when the canonical changes.
